version_description:
-Support for iOS 9
-Jabber to Jabber calling
-Ability to customize the ringtone for a call
-Ability to silence message notifications when in an active call
-Ability to edit the inputted number in keypad
-Expanded emoticon support
-User Experience Enhancements
-Stability Improvements

- Dial via Office - Reverse is supported over Mobile and Remote Access.
- Stability Improvements

-New App on Apple Watch, with this App you can:
* Check new chat messages
* Reply a chat with Siri, emoticons, and pre-defined messages.
* Answer/Decline/End a call
* Mute/Unmute a call
* Check recent calls
* Call back from resents
* Change your presence
-Send broadcast IM to multiple contacts
-Multiple Device Messaging (carbon copy to all connected Jabber clients) for cloud deployment
-Select speaker as default audio output deviceSecurity enhancements
-Stability improvements
-Refer to Release notes for more details

- 3D Touch support on home screen and chat list
- Enhancements on Apple Watch
* Answer or decline a second incoming call
* Resume a call on hold
* Delete chat messages
- Users can disable speaker for voice message
- Round avatar and presence icon
- Administrator can configure to make a call when a user taps on a contact
- IPv6 support
- Stability Improvements

- New look and feel
- Multiple Device Messaging for CUCM IM & Presence
- User option to disable VoIP capability over cellular network
- Support full landscape and portrait screen mode
- Support split view and slide over
- Added 10 more emojis
- View contact’s avatar in full screen
- Display custom contacts
- Security enhancements
- Stability Improvements

- Answer a Jabber call without unlocking screen
- Make a Jabber call from device native contacts
- Voicemail forwarding
- Call forwarding
- Custom HTML tabs
- Local calendar integration
- Saved chat list after relaunch
- Inline images in chat window
- Expanded device support
- Security enhancements
- Stability improvements

-Support push notification for instant messaging
-Stability improvements

-Support push notifications for voice and video calls
-Animated emoticons
-Significantly faster login experience
-Improved experience when making a call while chatting
-Stability improvements

-Toggle on or off Single Number Reach
-Unlock Jabber with Touch ID or Face ID
-Search Jabber contacts with Spotlight, and quickly initiate calls or chats
-Support push notification for managed file transfer
-Moved Meetings tab to Jabber home screen and changed tab name “Voice Messages” to “Voicemail”
-Access Internet web pages from Custom Tabs
-Added an option to ignore incoming calls when voicemail is not configured
-Dual Tone Multiple Frequency events “A, B, C, D” are supported during a call
-Support Jabber Bots with plain text messages
-Admins can configure different access policies for users connecting remotely
-More animated emoticons
-Security enhancements
-Stability improvements

- Support push notifications for AES end-to-end encryption messages
- Support push notifications for Jabber to Jabber call
- Support Jabber Bots with rich text messages
- Users can diagnose network error on mobile devices
- Persistent chat rooms on mobile clients(Beta)
- Expanded device support
- Stability improvements

- Support persistent chat rooms on mobile clients
- Expanded device support
- Stability improvements

-Support meeting control for Cisco Meeting Server(CMS) meeting
-Show participant list for Collaboration Meeting Rooms(CMR)
-Enhance sharing experience during a call
-User experience refresh
-iOS 12 Support
-Expanded device support
-Stability improvements

-A new operating mode: team messaging mode, the chat messages are persistent on the cloud
-Meeting controls for Webex CMR
-Webex Messenger interop with Webex Teams: support offline messages
-Cisco headset Bluetooth support
-Stability improvements

- Support viewing Microsoft OneDrive and SharePoint Online files for team messaging mode
- Stability improvements

Team messaging mode new features
- Send/receive Microsoft OneDrive and SharePoint Online files
- Quote message
- People Insights in Contact Cards: view rich, contextually relevant info about people you collaborate with
More Webex CMR meeting control features
- Assign host
- Admit people waiting in the lobby
- Mute/unmute all participants
Modern input box with quick actions
Stability improvements

Log out/log in the hunt group
Answer a call ringing on your coworker’s phone (call pickup)
Voicemail enhancements: Send/Reply/Reply to all, to one or more people/distribution lists
Team messaging mode new features - Custom contacts in the buddy list

- See the call notification earlier when Jabber is in the background

Dark mode
Enhanced meeting experience for Cisco Meeting Server
High availability enhancements for Calling and Messaging
